extends layout

block content
  .container.mt-5
    .text-center.mb-5
      h1.display-4.text-primary Young4Chicks
      p.lead.text-muted 
        | Is an urban brooder targeting youth between 18–30. Founded by the Youth Member of Parliament to 
        | stimulate wealth creation and money economy involvement.

    //- Business Section
    .row.mb-5
      .col-md-12
        h2.text-success How we Operate
        p
          | Young4ChickS sells chicks on request; layers and broilers. 
          | We provide both local and exotic breeds at a fixed price of UGX 1,650 per chick.
        ul
          li Each starter young farmer receives 100 chicks only.
          li Returning farmers can take up to 500 chicks.
          li Chicks cost UGX 1,650 each (fixed price).
          li Each farmer is eligible for 2 bags of feeds payable after 2 months.

    //- Users Section
    .row.mb-5
      .col-md-12
        h2.text-success Our Staff
        h4 Brooder Manager
        p
          | Oversees the brooder operations, manages chick stock, and approves or rejects requests.
          | Responsible for ensuring quality and availability of chicks.

        h4.mt-4 Sales Agents
        p
          | To attend to call-in requests from farmers. 


        h4.mt-4 And to you our clients, Youth Farmers
        p
          | Youth between 18–30 years old in the constituency. Must be registered with a 
          | recommender’s NIN number.


    //- Call to Action
    .text-center.mt-5
      a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg(href="/registration") Register Now
      a.btn.btn-outline-success.btn-lg.ms-3(href="/loginpage") Login